github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/comments/2978211674","html_url":"https://github.com/assertj/assertj/issues/3858#issuecomment-2978211674","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/3858","id":2978211674,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAIX3Vs6xg-da","user":{"login":"scordio","id":26772046,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2NzcyMDQ2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26772046?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio","html_url":"https://github.com/scordio","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-06-16T21:30:32Z","updated_at":"2025-06-16T21:30:32Z","body":"To avoid cluttering the API with all the possible use case combinations, we tend to favor navigation methods wherever possible.\n\nWhat do you think about having `withSuppressedExceptionsThat()`, which would allow chaining array assertions?\n\nSomething like:\n\n```java\nassertThatExceptionOfType(IOException.class)\n    .isThrownBy(System.out::println)\n    .withMessage(\"Retry policy for operation 'test' exhausted; aborting execution\")\n    .withCauseExactlyInstanceOf(IllegalStateException.class)\n    .withSuppressedExceptionsThat().satisfiesExactly(\n        suppressed1 -> assertThat(suppressed1).isExactlyInstanceOf(IOException.class),\n        suppressed2 -> assertThat(suppressed2).isExactlyInstanceOf(FileNotFoundException.class));\n```\n\nThe readability is not perfect between `withSuppressedExceptionsThat()` and `satisfiesExactly(...)`, but I think it's a general issue of `satisfiesExactly`:\n\n```java\nassertThat(values).satisfiesExactly(...)\n```","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/comments/2978211674/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"scordio","id":26772046,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2NzcyMDQ2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26772046?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio","html_url":"https://github.com/scordio","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"id":18191510667,"node_id":"UNE_lADOAIX3Vs67v6yvzwAAAAQ8TGyL","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/events/18191510667","actor":{"login":"scordio","id":26772046,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2NzcyMDQ2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26772046?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio","html_url":"https://github.com/scordio","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scordio/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"http